3. Architecture — Critical Facts (NEVER ASSUME OTHERWISE)

3.1 Processing Technology
- Pure JavaScript ONLY. No WebAssembly in any processing path.
- Core libraries: pdf.js, jsPDF, mammoth.js
- All conversion logic is pure JavaScript
- Any site references to "WebAssembly" are outdated and were removed from about.html, faq.html, llms.txt, llms-full.txt

3.2 Library Loading
- Libraries load from CDN (NOT local files):
  - Firebase 8.10.0 (sync, blocking)
  - jspdf 2.5.1 (defer)
  - pdf.js 3.11.174 (defer)
  - mammoth 1.6.0 (defer)
  - html2canvas 1.4.1 (defer)
- NO dynamic import(). All processing libraries download on every page load regardless of which tool is opened.
- App.js loads last after DOM
- Guards check typeof before conversion runs (toast if library not ready)

3.3 html2canvas Exception
- html2canvas loads dynamically on demand only via `document.createElement('script')` when Word Image mode is selected.
- It is NOT loaded via deferred script tag.
- There is NO standalone Screenshot-to-PDF tool.
- html2canvas is used only in `wordToPdfImage()`.

3.4 Routing & SEO
- Custom history-API SPA inside app.js. No framework.
- getRoute() reads window.location.pathname
- setRoute() calls history.pushState
- renderAppState() is central dispatcher
- updateSeoMeta() does pathname map lookup and writes directly to DOM (canonical, description, og tags, h1)
- Tool switching uses .tool-tab elements with data-tool attributes

3.5 HTML Structure
- Single-page app with auth modal, gallery vault, and PDF tool tabs
- app.html has robots meta noindex,follow intentionally (only accessible post-vault-login)
- Canonical tags use id="canonicalTag" for JS updates
- hreflang tags on some pages incorrectly list hi/es/ar pointing to same English URL — needs cleanup
- Inline script stripper removed from all pages, static canonical remains

3.6 Service Worker / PWA
- NO service worker. No sw.js. No manifest.json. No PWA registration.
- Offline capability (Airplane Mode Test) works purely via standard browser HTTP cache of CDN-loaded libraries
- If browser cache is cleared between visits, libraries must re-download before offline use works again
- NOT an engineered PWA offline strategy

3.7 HEIC Handling
- No separate HEIC library loaded
- Uses browser native createImageBitmap() or drawImage() on canvas
- Safari/iOS decodes HEIC natively
- Chrome/Firefox desktop may silently fail or produce blank pages (HEIC not natively supported)
- No WASM involved

3.8 CDN Sources
- Only cdnjs.cloudflare.com and gstatic.com — not jsDelivr or unpkg.

